<p></p>
<h1 id=3D"Loggingconfiguration-Introduction">Introduction</h1>
<p>The current implementation includes a logging mechanism for debugging pu=
rposes in development environments, which monitors <a class=3D"external-lin=
k" href=3D"http://stash.tedivm.com/" rel=3D"nofollow">Stash</a>, introduced=
 in <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://github.com/tedivm/TedivmStas=
hBundle" rel=3D"nofollow">Stash-bundle</a>, and the <span><a href=3D"/displ=
ay/EZP/Persistence+cache+configuration">persistence cache</a> mechanism</sp=
an>.</p>
<p>Logging is enabled by default, except for the production environment to =
avoid excessive memory usage on production environments.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"Loggingconfiguration-Usageexample">Usage example</h1>
<p>StashBundle logging, represented by the <code>stash.logging</code> setti=
ng, and persistence cache logging, represented by the setting <code>paramet=
ers.ezpublish.spi.persistence.cache.persistenceLogger.enableCallLogging</co=
de>, and are both enabled by default on development environments.<br>Both s=
ettings expect a boolean value (<code>true</code> or <code>false</code>), s=
o, if you desire to turn off the logging mechanism you can use the followin=
g configuration in <code>ezpublish_dev.yml</code>:<br><br></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>ezpublish_dev.yml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">stash:
    logging: false
    caches:
        default:
            handlers:
                - FileSystem
            inMemory: false
            registerDoctrineAdapter: false

parameters:
    ezpublish.spi.persistence.cache.persistenceLogger.enableCallLogging: fa=
lse</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Be aware that using stash logging and persistence cache logging will req=
uire additional memory. This should be used for debugging purposes only.</p=
>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"Loggingconfiguration-Errorloggingandrotation">Error logging and r=
otation</h2>
<p>eZ Publish uses the Monolog component to log errors, and it has a <code>=
RotatingFileHandler</code> that allows for file rotation.</p>
<p>According to their documentation, it "logs records to a file and creates=
 one logfile per day. It will also delete files older than <code>$maxFiles<=
/code>".</p>
<p>But then, their own recommendation is to use "<code>logrotate</code>" in=
stead of doing the rotation in the handler as you would have better perform=
ance.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>More details here:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/Seldaek/monolog" class=3D"external-link" =
rel=3D"nofollow"> https://github.com/Seldaek/monolog</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"http://linuxcommand.org/man_pages/logrotate8.html" class=3D"=
external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://linuxcommand.org/man_pages/logrotate=
8.html</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>If you decided to use Monolog's handler, it can be configured in <code>/=
ezpublish/config/config.yml</code></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">monolog:
    handlers:
        main:
            type: rotating_file
            max_files: 10
            path: "%kernel.logs_dir%/%kernel.environment%.log"
            level: debug</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
    </div>
